 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffsterinsf>jeffsterinsf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 10:43:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1278.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: nOOb who needs equipment advice</span><hr size=1> First suggestion -- go complete your newb armor where you have gaps-- it is actually pretty decent and should be a cakewalk for you to get.<br>
<br>
Stein of Moggok is a MUST with Int+10 and SVD+25.  About 200-250 pp (Bazaar PC Trader sell prices on Veeshan).  Used one into my 50s. Significantly better secondary pieces run around 5-15 kpp or a crowd of 50s players to complete a quest (Phenocryst's Focus -- don't kill Geonids for plat -- will make sense one day).<br>
<br>
I would look into a Black *Alloy* Medallion for Mana Preservation III, good through level 44 spells, as I recall. About 250 pp on a good day, 400-500 pp otherwise. I am assuming that you are already using at least the summoned earring and bracer for their mana reduction and DD increase. They don't stack, but complement each other. Sometime an Enshrouded Veil (about 750-1000 pp) will be a mainstay, all the way up as may eventually chose to canipet using 49 Earth.<br>
<br>
Get your Int up first -- you probably won't need much in the way of resists until in your 40s, from my experience. The few things that will hit you annoyingly are generally aviodable (wurmspores in EC come to mind, as well as staying away from undead zones like Unrest). Even if you do get hit, your summoned bandages can usually keep up with the DoT with decent Bind Wound skill. Target 200-220 Int, unbuffed, the mana pool gains beyond 200 are slower, and do not leverage the level-multiplier effect (SFAIK, according to Mage Compendium and how Magelo behaves). Once into the 50s, 230-ish is usually ok as KEI will max you at 255, until you get PoP AAs that allow a higher cap.<br>
<br>
Froglok Bonecaster's Robe is a nice robe upgrade, still wearing in my 50s until I can get a Skyshrine Robe. Prices have been falling recently, now down to about 1500 pp on a good day!<br>
<br>
I spent time daily in the bazaar looking for items for slots by Int, with a price cap of a couple thousand pp until I knew what was out there and what a good price was. Lots of notes, but prices on now-low-end gear have been falling as more and more Planar gear gets into the world and we lucky ones can get hand-me-downs. Was just grouped with a player who has been in Norrath since beta and got quite a smile from my Froglok Bonecaster's Robe -- he tells me they used to be 10-20 kpp pieces and in HIGH demand as one of the top robes for casters in the game.<br>
<br>
Not cheap, but the 9 kpp horse is a MUST if you solo a lot or play without KEI. I bought an Earring of the Solstice thinking the FT1 was the best thing since slice bread. Then I realized that the difference between sitting and standing medding was FT20 -- and no additional aggro from sitting! No advice on dino vs. horse yet.<br>
<br>
GL -- have fun -- buy low, use it for a while, sell high -- faster to make plat than loot, and you can XP on MOBs that drop squat. By the time I hit my late 20s, people thought I had been twinked...<br>
<br>
